&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;&lt;!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --&gt;&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;DIV&gt;Some distance away, out of the immediate battle a small group of ships hang nearly motionless in the air, cloaked from prying sensors. &lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&quot;They don&#39;t seem to be ready for us?&quot; The firm voice of Scourge could be heard quietly.&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&quot;No, they don&#39;t. How interesting.&quot; Came Cyclonus&#39; measured reply. &quot;I would have thought that after our last attack they would have a better response to this same attack strategy.&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&quot;What about that new guy, the one with all the fire power?&quot;&nbsp;Scourge asked eagerly, &quot;I want him.&quot;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&quot;Perhaps, Scourge, but not yet.&quot; Cyclonus paused and then continued, &quot;Have the sweeps picked up Rodimus&#39; signal?&quot;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&quot;No.&quot;&nbsp;Scourge replied somewhat dejectedly, although if it was because of his faliure to find Rodimus or because he would have to wait to attack his quarry it is difficult to tell. &quot;He doesn&#39;t seem to be here.&quot;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cyclonus was silent for a moment and then spoke, &quot;Take a few of the remaining sweep and find him, perhaps he has left the base. Without his matrix perhaps he is more cowardly than I had thought.&quot;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;Scourge grunted once as he thought of the changes Cyclonus had undergone since he had absorbed the Matrix from Rodimus Prime, some of the changes they had both gone through since then. The new Minions were not the only ones to have benefited from the powers granted by the Matrix. &lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&quot;Yes sir.&quot; Scourge finally said, acknowledging the order from Cyclonus. &quot;On my way.&quot; &lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;With a blast of power Scourge and a few sweeps left Cyclonus&#39; position and began a search for thier elusive prey.&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cyclonus on the other hand hung in the air a powerful predator waiting for the moment to attack, and yet wise enough to know that it was not yet. For the moment he would let the sweeps soften up thier target as he waited, the time would come soon . .&nbsp; yes very soon. &lt;/DIV&gt;
&lt;DIV&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;
